Count 1 - Possess THC (2nd +offense) - No contest plea.   Convicted.  State moves to dismiss and read in count 2, possess drug paraphernalia as repeater.  Motion granted.  Sentence is withheld.  Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for two (2) years.  Conditions of probation are:
1) AODA assessment and follow through;
2) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
3) Pay costs of action;
4) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
5) Maintain full-time employment/schooling combination;
6) Spend thirty (30) days in jail, under the Huber Law, to commence on 07-10-14 at 6:00 p.m.  
7) Provide DNA sample.   
